<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>ReferVo Inc ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application and website (collectively, the "Service").</p>
<p>By using ReferVo, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not access or use our Service.</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We collect information that you provide directly to us, as well as information collected automatically when you use our Service.</p>

<p><strong>Information You Provide:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Account information (name, email address, phone number)</li>
  <li>Business information (company name, industry, location)</li>
  <li>Payment information (processed securely through Stripe; we do not store payment card details)</li>
  <li>Profile information (professional bio, services offered)</li>
  <li>Referral data (leads sent, received, and associated notes)</li>
  <li>In-app messages sent to your connections</li>
  <li>Communications with us or other users</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Information Collected Automatically:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Device information (device type, operating system, unique device identifiers)</li>
  <li>Log information (access times, pages viewed, IP address)</li>
  <li>Location information (with your consent)</li>
  <li>Usage data (features used, interactions within the app)</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our Service</li>
  <li>Process transactions and send related information</li>
  <li>Connect you with other professionals for referral opportunities</li>
  <li>Enable messaging between you and your business connections</li>
  <li>Send you technical notices, updates, and support messages</li>
  <li>Respond to your comments, questions, and customer service requests</li>
  <li>Monitor and analyze trends, usage, and activities</li>
  <li>Detect, investigate, and prevent fraudulent transactions and other illegal activities</li>
  <li>Personalize and improve your experience</li>
  <li>Send push notifications related to your account activity (with your consent)</li>
</ul>

<h2>In-App Messaging</h2>
<p>ReferVo allows users to send short messages (up to 100 characters) to their established business connections within the app. Regarding these messages:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Messages are stored securely on our servers</li>
  <li>Messages are only visible to the sender and intended recipient</li>
  <li>We do not share, sell, or use message content for advertising purposes</li>
  <li>Messages are retained as long as your account remains active</li>
  <li>You may request deletion of your messages by contacting us</li>
</ul>
<p>Messaging is only available between users who have an established connection through the app. You cannot message users you are not connected with.</p>

<h2>Payment Information and Stripe</h2>
<p>ReferVo uses Stripe to process payments. When you add a payment method or set up a Stripe account through ReferVo:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Payment card information is collected and processed directly by Stripe</li>
  <li>ReferVo does not store or have access to your full card numbers</li>
  <li>Stripe may collect additional information as described in their <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a></li>
  <li>Transaction records are shared between ReferVo and Stripe for record-keeping and dispute resolution</li>
</ul>

<h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
<p>We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>With Other Users:</strong> Information you choose to share as part of referrals (such as lead details and professional profiles) will be visible to relevant partners. Messages you send will be delivered to your intended recipients.</li>
  <li><strong>Payment Processors:</strong> We share necessary information with Stripe to process payments and maintain your connected account.</li>
  <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may share information with third-party vendors who perform services on our behalf.</li>
  <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> We may disclose information if required by law or in response to valid legal requests.</li>
  <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred.</li>
  <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> We may share information with your explicit consent.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Security</h2>
<p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.</p>

<h2>Data Retention</h2>
<p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide the Service and fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy. Transaction records may be retained for longer periods as required for tax, legal, or compliance purposes. In-app messages are retained as long as your account is active or until you request their deletion.</p>

<h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
<p>Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal information we hold about you</li>
  <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
  <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal information, including messages</li>
  <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Request a copy of your data in a portable format</li>
  <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Opt out of marketing communications and push notifications at any time</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@refervo.com">support@refervo.com</a>.</p>

<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>Our Service is not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

<h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.</p>

<h2>Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
